Files maintained by the git repository
======================================
COPYING             GPLv3 license text
FAQ                 Frequently Asked Questions (and corresponding answers)
Makefile            root Makefile, among others useful to build gcc
cl/                 source codes of Code Listener and its gcc front-end
cl/README           more specific README for the source codes of cl
fa/                 source codes of Forester


Files maintained locally only
=============================
cl_build/           working directory for build of libcl.so
fa_build/           working directory for build of libfa.so
gcc                 symlink to gcc internal headers (feel free to override)
gcc-build/          working directory for build of gcc
gcc-install/        location of the installed gcc after a successful build
gcc-src/            symlink to (or SVN working copy of) gcc sources


Useful targets of the root Makefile
===================================
all                 run 'make' in cl and fa (default)
check               run 'make check' in cl and fa
distcheck           run 'make distcheck' in cl and fa
build_gcc           build gcc from the released tarball
build_gcc_svn       build gcc from SVN sources (NOTE: this may take some time)
